Example Scenario – EMI Recalculation After Purchase

Create an example flow demonstrating how the offline purchase functionality works.

Membership Plan:

Gold Purchase Plan

Plan Amount = ₹1,00,000
Monthly EMI = ₹10,000
Duration = 12 months

Customer has already paid:

5 installments

Total Paid:

₹50,000

Admin records jewellery purchase:

Gold Necklace – ₹1,20,000
Gold Ring – ₹80,000

Total Purchase Amount:

₹2,00,000

System calculation:

Outstanding Balance =
₹2,00,000 − ₹50,000

Outstanding Balance =
₹1,50,000

Remaining Months =
12 − 5 = 7

New EMI =
₹1,50,000 ÷ 7 ≈ ₹21,428 per month

After saving the purchase:

Payment Summary updates automatically

Membership Listing shows the updated EMI

Purchase History displays the newly recorded purchase

